Your connection with Aubay starts in the following lines:
Aubay Portugal is a French multinational company that has been operating in the country since 2007, with offices in Lisbon and Porto. We are a leading technology consultancy with a presence in seven European Union countries, specializing in the management, implementation, development and maintenance of information systems.
With more than 150 active partners, we operate in strategic sectors such as banking, insurance, automotive, aviation, telecommunications, services and energy, driving innovation and digital transformation.
Excellence, proximity and innovation are the pillars that distinguish us and enable us to support companies in building technological solutions that make a difference.
What are we looking for?
4+ years of professional experience as an Automation Tester (Mid/Senior level);
Mandatory expertise in UFT;
Strong knowledge of Cucumber; familiarity with Playwright is a plus;
Solid experience designing and implementing non-regression test automation, particularly for Salesforce applications;
Fluent in French.
What do we have to offer you?
Comprehensive health insurance, including dental coverage;
Feedback&Coffee – our integrated performance management system, with regular feedback sessions and a structured Career Progression Model;
Aubay Training Academy, designed for your development: technical and behavioural training (in-class and e-learning), Meet&Techs, Webinars, Mentoring and Technology Centers;
Events and team building activities that strengthen team spirit and promote closeness;
Digital platform for mental health and emotional well-being, with free psychology consultations, so you can take care of yourself at any time;
Health and well-being programme, with workshops and initiatives for our employees and other activities open to the community;
We grow with you and your family - we offer a Mini-Aubilous Kit when your children are born and annual support for school supplies, from pre-school to higher education;
Language platform, with conversation classes in 12 languages;
Working model: hybrid.
What makes us different?
Our organisational culture is based on solid values: commitment, excellence, team spirit, well-being, happiness and empathy;
We value and recognise those who are part of our history, with referral awards and a special birthday gift;
We believe in authenticity: we don't have a dress code, because what matters is talent and attitude;
We promote closeness and an informal environment;
Here, you will grow in good company, because we believe that professional development also means sharing experiences and building relationships.
Your next adventure starts here!
If you can see yourself growing with us, take the first step and send your CV to:
ana.c.jorge@aubay.pt
The future is waiting for you — and so are we!
